TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,10,1);
$c = 6/$a**3;


BEGIN_TEXT

You'll need to use the formatted text mode in order to do this problem: click the "formatted text" button on the bottom of
the page and then click "submit answers". $PAR

Let \(X\) be a random variable with probability density function 

\[ f(x) = \left\{ "\{"; \} \begin{array}{ll}
c($a x-x^2) & \mbox{if \ } 0<x<$a \cr
0           & \mbox{otherwise}
\end{array} \right. \]

Find the value of \(c\): $BR

\(c = \)\{ans_rule(10)\} $BR

Find the cumulative distribution function of \(X\):

\[ F(x) = \left\{ "\{"; \} \begin{array}{ll}
\{tex_ans_rule(10)\} & \mbox{if \ } x \le 0 \cr
\{tex_ans_rule(10)\} & \mbox{if \ } 0<x<$a \cr
\{tex_ans_rule(10)\} & \mbox{if \ } x \ge $a 
\end{array} \right. \]

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($c));
ANS(fun_cmp(0));
ANS(fun_cmp("$c*($a*(x**2)/2 - (x**3)/3)"));
ANS(fun_cmp(1));

